ner]]\n|-\n| [[2007 Champ Car season|2007]]\n|[[ESPN on ABC|ABC]]\n|[[Jon Beekhuis]]\n|[[Bill Stephens]] <br> [[Cameron Steele]] <br> [[Michelle Beisner]]\n|-\n| [[2018 IndyCar Series season|2018]]\n| [[NBCSN]]\n| rowspan=2 |[[Leigh Diffey]]\n| rowspan=2 |[[Townsend Bell]] <br> [[Paul Tracy]]\n| [[Katie Hargitt]] <br> [[Kevin Lee (broadcaster)|Kevin Lee]] <br> [[Robin Miller (journalist)|Robin Miller]] <br> [[Jon Beekhuis]]\n|-\n| [[2019 IndyCar Series|2019]]\n| [[NBC]]\n| [[Kevin Lee (broadcaster)|Kevin Lee]] <br> Dillon Welch <br> [[Robin Miller (journalist)|Robin Miller]] <br> [[Jon Beekhuis]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.globaleventsgrouppdx.com/champ_car/index.html Official Site]\n{{sequence\n|prev = [[Bommarito Automotive Group 500]]\n|list = [[IndyCar Series]]<br>Grand Prix of Portland\n|next = [[IndyCar Monterey Grand Prix]]\n}}\n{{Grand Prix of Portland}}\n{{Sporting events in Portland, Oregon}}\n{{IndyCar Series races}}\n\n{{coord|45|35|49|N|122|41|45|W|region:US-OR_type:event|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Grand Prix of Portland| ]]\n[[Category:Recurring sporting events established in 1984]]\n[[Category:Recurring events disestablished in 2007]]\n[[Category:1984 establishments in Oregon]]\n[[Category:Sports in Portland, Oregon]]\n[[Category:Annual events in Portland, Oregon]]\n", "text_old": "{{About||the sports car race|Portland Grand Prix}}\n{{Infobox motor race\n|Race title = Grand Prix of Portland\n|Logo = [[File:GPPortland logo.png]]\n|Track map = [[File:Portland international raceway.svg|200px]]\n|Series long = [[IndyCar Series]]\n|Series short = ICS\n|Venue = [[Portland International Raceway]]\n|Sponsor = none\n|First race = 1984\n|First series race = 2018\n|Last race = \n|Distance = {{convert|200.463|mi|km|abbr=on}}\n|Laps = 102\n|Duration = \n|Previous names = '''Stroh's 200''' (1984\u20131985)<br />'''Budweiser/G.I. Joe's 200''' (1986, 1988\u20131992, 1994)<br>'''Budweiser/G.I. Joe's 200 Presented by Texaco''' (1987, 1993, 1995\u20131999)<br>'''Freightliner/G.I. Joe's 200 Presented by Texaco''' (2000\u20132001)<br>'''G.I. Joe's 200''' (2002\u20132003)<br>'''Champ Car Grand Prix of Portland''' (2004)<br>'''G.I. Joe's Grand Prix of Portland''' (2005\u20132006)<br>'''Mazda Grand Prix of Portland''' (2007)\n|Most wins driver = [[Michael Andretti]] (3)<br>[[Al Unser, Jr.]] (3)\n|Most wins team = [[Newman/Haas Racing]] (8)\n|Most wins manufacturer = '''Chassis:''' [[Lola Cars|Lola]] (12)<br>'''Engine:''' Ford/Cosworth (6)<br>[[Chevrolet]] (6)\n}}\nThe '''Grand Prix of Portland''' is an [[Indy Car Series]] race held at [[Portland International Raceway]] in [[Portland, Oregon]]. The race was held every year from 1984 through 2007 first as a [[Champ Car|CART]] series race, then as part of [[Champ Car World Series]]. After a ten-year absence, the race returned to the IndyCar Series for the [[2018 IndyCar Series|2018 season]].<ref>{{cite news|title=IndyCar racing will return to Portland International Raceway on Labor Day weekend 2018|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/sports/index.ssf/2017/10/indycar_racing_returns_to_port.html|first=Molly|last=Blue|work=[[The Oregonian]]|publisher=[[Advance Publications]]|date=October 12, 2017|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n\nPortland is best-remembered as being the site of two of the closest finishes on a [[Road racing|road course]] in [[American Championship car racing|Indy car racing]] history. In 1986, [[Michael Andretti]] lost fuel pressure on the final turn of the final lap, which allowed his father [[Mario Andretti|Mario]] to catch up and beat him to the finish line by 0.070 seconds. At the time, it was the closest finish of any race in Indy car history. In 1997, in a three-wide finish, [[Mark Blundell]] beat second place [[Gil de Ferran]] by 0.027 seconds, and beat third place [[Raul Boesel]] by 0.055 seconds. For a road course race, it was the all-time closest finish in CART series history, as well as the closest three-car finish in series history. \n\nFor nearly its entire existence, the title sponsor of the race was [[G.I. Joe's|G.I. Joe's sporting goods and auto parts]] store, and the event was held during or around the [[Portland Rose Festival]]. Numerous times, the race was held on [[Father's Day (United States)|Father's Day]]. Beginning in 2018, the race was held in September on [[Labor Day]] weekend, promoted by [[Kim Green|Green]] [[Kevin Savoree|Savoree]] Racing Promotions.\n\n==Race winners==\n===IndyCar Series===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Date\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Driver\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Team\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Chassis\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Engine\n! colspan=\"2\"|Race Distance\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Race Time\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Average Speed<br>(mph)\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Report\n|-\n! Laps\n! Miles (km)\n|-\n!colspan=11|[[Champ Car|CART/Champ Car World Series]]\n|-\n!colspan=11|{{convert|1.915|mi|km}} course\n|-\n! [[1984 IndyCar season|1984]]\n| June 17\n| {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Al Unser Jr.]]\n| [[Galles Racing]]\n| [[March Engineering|March]] 84C\n| [[Cosworth]]\n|align=\"center\"|104\n|align=\"center\"|199.16 (320.516)\n|align=\"center\"|1:53:17\n|align=\"center\"|105.484\n| [[1984 Stroh's 200|Report]]\n|-\n! [[1985 IndyCar season|1985]]\n| June 16\n| {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Mario Andretti]]\n| [[Newman/Haas Racing]]\n| [[Lola Cars|Lola]] T900\n| [[Cosworth]]\n|align=\"center\"|104\n|align=\"center\"|199.16 (320.516)\n|align=\"center\"|1:51:35\n|align=\"center\"|107.083\n| [[1985 Stroh's 200|Report]]\n|-\n! [[1986 IndyCar season|1986]]\n| June 15\n| {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Mario Andretti]]\n| [[Newman/Haas Racing]]\n| [[Lola Cars|Lola]] T8600\n| [[Cosworth]]\n|align=\"center\"|104\n|align=\"center\"|199.16 (320.516)\n|align=\"center\"|1:50:53\n|align=\"center\"|107.759\n| [[1986 Budweiser/G.I. Joe's 200|Report]]\n|-\n! [[1987 IndyCar season|1987]]\n| June 14\n| {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Bobby Rahal]]\n| [[Truesports]]\n| [[Lola Cars|Lola]] T8700\n| [[Cosworth]]\n|align=\"center\"|104\n|align=\"center\"|199.16 (320.516)\n|align=\"center\"|1:50:02\n|align=\"center\"|108.59\n| [[1987 Budweiser/G.I. Joe's 200|Report]]\n|-\n!colspan=11|{{convert|1.922|mi|km}} course\n|-\n! [[1988 IndyCar season|1988]]\n| June 19\n| {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Danny Sullivan]]\n| [[Penske Racing]]\n| [[Penske Racing|Penske]] PC-17\n| [[Chevrolet]]-[[Ilmor]]\n|align=\"center\"|104\n|align=\"center\"|199.888 (321.688)\n|align=\"center\"|1:57:17\n|align=\"center\"|102.253\n| [[1988 Budweiser/G.I. Joe's 200|Report]]\n|-\n! [[1989 IndyCar season|1989]]\n| June 25\n| {{Flagicon|BRA}} [[Emerson Fittipaldi]]\n| [[Patrick Racing]]\n| [[Penske Racing|Penske]] PC-18\n| [[Chevrolet]]-[[Ilmor]]\n|align=\"center\"|104\n|align=\"center\"|199.888 (321.688)\n|align=\"center\"|1:55:20\n|align=\"center\"|103.984\n| [[1989 Budweiser/G.I. Joe's 200|Report]]\n|-\n! [[1990 IndyCar season|1990]]\n| June 24\n| {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Michael Andretti]]\n| [[Newman/Haas Racing]]\n| [[Lola Cars|Lola]] T9000\n| [[Chevrolet]]-[[Ilmor]]\n|align=\"center\"|104\n|align=\"center\"|199.888 (321.688)\n|align=\"center\"|1:48:22\n|align=\"center\"|110.643\n| [[1990 Budweiser/G.I. Joe's 200|Report]]\n|-\n! [[1991 IndyCar season|1991]]\n| June 23\n| {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Michael Andretti]]\n| [[Newman/Haas Racing]]\n| [[Lola Cars|Lola]] T9100\n| [[Chevrolet]]-[[Ilmor]]\n|align=\"center\"|104\n|align=\"center\"|199.888 (321.688)\n|align=\"center\"|1:44:06\n|align=\"center\"|115.208\n| [[1991 Budweiser/G.I. Joe's 200|Report]]\n|-\n!colspan=11|{{convert|1.95|mi|km}} course\n|-\n! [[1992 IndyCar season|1992]]\n| June 21\n| {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Michael Andretti]]\n| [[Newman/Haas Racing]]\n| [[Lola Cars|Lola]] T9200\n| [[Ford-Cosworth]] XB\n|align=\"center\"|102\n|align=\"center\"|198.9 (320.098)\n|align=\"center\"|1:53:25\n|align=\"center\"|105.219\n| [[1992 Budweiser/G.I. Joe's 200|Report]]\n|-\n! [[1993 IndyCar season|1993]]\n| June 27\n| {{Flagicon|BRA}} [[Emerson Fittipaldi]]\n| [[Penske Racing